Former president Jacob Zuma's son, Duduzane is back for the second day at the State Capture Inquiry. Zuma dismissed all allegations made about him. JOHANNESBURG - Duduzane Zuma was back on the stand for the second day at the state capture inquiry. On Monday, he rubbished every witness testimony that implicated him in state capture. The son of the former president, Jacob Zuma said all those who have testified about him met the Gupta brothers willingly. That includes former deputy finance minister, Mcebisi Jonas. Zuma said Jonas knew when and where the meeting to discuss his taking over of the finance portfolio would be held.